      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BENNIE AND THE JETS NZ (5) has been hard to fault of late and made it two wins in a row when racing parked before cruising home by 15m at his latest appearance at Melton. Draws wider but owns a good record here so could deliver again. QUIRKY CHARACTER (7) raced parked and faded last time but placed from this barrier at Melton prior. He was racking up the wins earlier in his campaign so will be hard to stop if he shows his best form. KEAYANG KURKI (2) appeared most recently when she closed last prep with a win at Group 1 level in the Breeders Crown 3F Final at Melton. Owns a good record at this circuit and distance and has won two of three fresh attempts. Draws well and should be ready off two trials. NEPHEW OF SONOKO (6) draws wider but did a good job in finishing runner-up at Melton last time out.",
